Anna Okon Security firm, Hogan Guards Limited, has announced the appointment of Mr Paul Ibirogba as its Chief Executive Officer. It added that this move was part of its strategic diversification and expansion plan. It said the new CEO is a marketing and human relations expert with vast experience in organisational management, cost control and business development, adding that he had been involved in community outreach and education coaching. He will oversee the company comprising over 8,000 employees, which is currently being transformed into a holding conglomerate with five new subsidiaries, the firm noted in a statement on Tuesday. The statement read in part, “A graduate of University of Houston, Texas, where he studied Communications, Ibirogba also majored in Business Administration at the Morgan State University. “His working experience traverses North America and Asia where he has had leading roles in education business engagement especially in China, South Korea and the Philippines.” The new Hogan Guards CEO is said to be an experienced Vector marketing agent in Maryland, United States of America and had been involved in outreach coordination in Houston. The statement added that Ibirogba was a former employee of the City of Fargo, North Dakota where he provided social services for vulnerable individuals and organisations. He was the former editor of Vegan World News, United States, between 2018 and 2019, the statement added. Copyright PUNCH.
